      <hedline>
        <hl1>Too Hot in Washington</hl1>
        <hl2 class="online_headline">Too Hot in Washington</hl2>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jill Hacker letter on Bob Herbert's June 24 column agrees global warming debate is missing sense of urgency despite Washington area heat alerts</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert (''How Hot Is Too Hot?,'' column, June 24) is exactly right: the global warming debate is missing a sense of urgency.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="online_lead_paragraph">
        <p>Too Hot in Washington To the Editor:.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert (''How Hot Is Too Hot?,'' column, June 24) is exactly right: the global warming debate is missing a sense of urgency.</p>
        <p>Here in the Washington area, while the president brushes aside a report on the issue, we are warned that heat makes it dangerous to go out. Progressively hotter summers have become the norm.</p>
        <p>Oh, well, I guess the kids don't really need to go to the playground anyway.</p>
        <p>JILL HACKER  Reston, Va., June 24, 2002</p>
      </block>
